      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 40
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically sorted 1993 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine. This chassis retains its legendary 50/50 weight distribution and double-wishbone suspension geometry, providing exceptional lateral grip and feedback. The sequential turbo transition is linear and predictable, indicating a healthy solenoid rack and vacuum system\u2014which has been proactively refreshed with high-temp silicone lines. To address the platform's thermal management requirements, a high-capacity aluminum radiator and upgraded AST have been installed. The 5-speed manual transmission delivers crisp engagement through all gates, and the Torsen limited-slip differential remains tight. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the structural integrity is excellent, and the drivetrain produces strong, consistent boost pressure without signs of premature apex seal wear. A high-performance driver\u2019s example ready for immediate spirited use.",
      "price": 36500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
